commitResults.messageTitle: [Level 0. Rename, Greet, Exit] (a) Changed chatbot name form Duke to Edna (b) Implement an initial skeletal version
[Level 1. Echo] Improve the skeletal version of Edna so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye.
[Level 2. Add, List] Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
[Level 3. Mark as Done] (a) Create Task class. (b) Add the ability to mark tasks as done. (c) Add the ability to change the status back to not done.

[Level 4. ToDos, Events, Deadlines] Add support for tracking three types of tasks: ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time e.g., (a) team project meeting 2/10/2019 2-4pm (b) orientation week 4/10/2019 to 11/10/2019
commitResults.messageBody: * Fixed Level 3 error for mixing up "X" and " " for marked and unmarked tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: [Automated Text UI Testing] Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
[Level 5. Handle Errors] Teach the chatbot to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
commitResults.messageBody:
Use Exceptions to handle errors
Define a class DukeException to represent exceptions specific to Duke.

commitResults.messageBody:
Level 0. Rename, Greet, Exit
(a) Rename chatbot to "Edna-Duke".
(b) Implement an initial skeletal version of the it that simply greets the user and exits.

commitResults.messageTitle: [Level 1. Echo] Improve the skeletal version of Duke so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye.
[Level 2. Add, List] Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
[Level 3. Mark as Done] Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.

[Level 4. ToDos, Events, Deadlines] Add support for tracking three types of tasks: - ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park - Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm - Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time   e.g., (a) team project meeting 2/10/2019 2-4pm (b) orientation week 4/10/2019 to 11/10/2019
